Following the injuries copped during the international friendly and AFCON qualifiers, the Super Eagles duo of William Troost-Ekong and Innocent Bonke have both returned to their bases in Europe. Defender and deputy skipper Troost-Ekong suffered a groin strain in the 2-1 defeat of Sierra Leone in Abuja on Thursday during the AFCON Qualifiers, while midfielder Bonke got injured in the friendly game against Mexico in Dallas on May 28.   2023 AFCON Qualifiers:  Peseiro eyes second win against Sao…     Mauritius 2022 : Minister commends Team Nigeria ‘s…     Mikel rewards youngsters at Back2Base Talent Hunt   The Watford defender returned to England while Bonke returned to France to attend to the injuries. Meanwhile, coach Jose Peseiro said he hopes to replace the injured Troost-Ekong in the centre back with another member of the team. “Ekong is not here but I have other players, I have other centre-backs. Of course, we want to improve our defensive process and we should be able to play a good centre-back,” he added.